<!-- Hero -->
<section class="section-hero section-hero--dark">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="section-hero__headline">AHG Doesn't React to Policy.<br>AHG Writes It.</h1>
    <p class="section-hero__sub">Six fights. Every young person aged 14 to 26.</p>
    <a href="#agenda" class="btn btn-outline btn-outline--light">SEE THE AGENDA</a>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Three Pillars -->
<section class="section-pillars" id="agenda">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-pillars__label">THE THREE PILLARS</span>
    <h2 class="section-pillars__headline">The Fights We Picked</h2>
    <div class="card-grid card-grid--three">
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card__number">01</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Education Is Broken</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Built for compliance, not comprehension. We're rewriting what school means for the students it leaves behind.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card__number">02</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Protection, Not Paperwork</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Foster care, mental health, housing, juvenile justice. Every system touching young lives needs someone in the room who won't leave.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <span class="card__number">03</span>
        <h3 class="card__title">Nothing About Us Without Us</h3>
        <p class="card__text">If nobody at the table has lived it, the table is lying. We put people closest to the problem closest to the power.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Six Policy Issues -->
<section class="section-policy-issues" id="issues">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-policy-issues__label">THE SIX FIGHTS</span>
    <h2 class="section-policy-issues__headline">The Agenda</h2>

    <div class="policy-accordion">

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">01</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Mental Health in Schools</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>Every school. A licensed counselor. Every day. Not shared across buildings. Not once a week.</strong></p>
            <p>Kids are in crisis and the infrastructure to catch them doesn't exist. We fight for mandatory counselor-to-student ratios, trauma-informed training for all staff, and state funding that treats adolescent mental health as non-negotiable.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">02</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Education Redesign</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>The curriculum was built for a world that's gone. Time to build one for the world students actually inherit.</strong></p>
            <p>Financial literacy requirements. Civics beyond textbooks. Career pathways starting in middle school. Student voices in curriculum review at district and state level. All of it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item" id="foster-care">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">03</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Foster Care Transition</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>No one should age out of a system with nothing. The state that raised them owes them a real transition.</strong></p>
            <div class="policy-accordion__stats">
              <div class="policy-accordion__stat">
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-number">38,000+</span>
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-label">kids in TX foster care</span>
              </div>
              <div class="policy-accordion__stat">
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-number">1.5%</span>
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-label">earn a degree by 24</span>
              </div>
              <div class="policy-accordion__stat">
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-number">46%</span>
                <span class="policy-accordion__stat-label">homeless before 26</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p>Extended benefits to 25. Guaranteed housing for aging-out youth. Mentorship mandates. State-funded transition coordinators who stay with young people through the entire process. No exceptions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">04</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Juvenile Justice</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>A child who enters the justice system should leave it better. Right now, the opposite is true.</strong></p>
            <p>Diversion-first models. End juvenile solitary. Automatic record expungement at 18 for non-violent offenses. Restorative justice as default in every jurisdiction.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">05</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Youth Representation</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>Decisions about young people are made every day in rooms without a single young person present. Done.</strong></p>
            <p>Youth advisory boards with binding authority. Lower the age for appointed commission seats. Paid civic fellowships placing 18-to-26-year-olds in government offices with real influence.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="policy-accordion__item">
        <button class="policy-accordion__trigger" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="policy-accordion__number">06</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__title">Housing Access</span>
          <span class="policy-accordion__icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="policy-accordion__panel" hidden>
          <div class="policy-accordion__content">
            <p class="policy-accordion__position"><strong>You can't build a life without a stable place to live. Housing is infrastructure.</strong></p>
            <p>Guaranteed transitional housing for aging-out foster youth. Co-signer alternative programs. Rental assistance tied to enrollment or employment. Zoning reform that creates affordable inventory for young adults in urban centers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Advocacy -->
<section class="section-advocacy" id="advocacy">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-advocacy__inner">
      <span class="section-advocacy__label">ADVOCACY</span>
      <h2 class="section-advocacy__headline">Policy Without Pressure Is a Suggestion.</h2>
      <p class="section-advocacy__text">We show up. Hearings, councils, statehouses. We draft language, build coalitions, and name officials who block progress. This isn't performance. This is the work.</p>
      <a href="/get-involved" class="btn btn-primary">JOIN THE FIGHT</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.querySelectorAll('.policy-accordion__trigger').forEach(function(trigger) {
    trigger.addEventListener('click', function() {
      var expanded = this.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
      var panel = this.nextElementSibling;
      var icon = this.querySelector('.policy-accordion__icon');

      this.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!expanded));
      panel.hidden = expanded;
      icon.textContent = expanded ? '+' : '–';
    });
  });
</script>
